6\n  Linear SVC               : 0.7854\n\nINSIGHT 3 — Class Imbalance Effect:\n  Original Neutral class   : 58.1% → would bias all predictions\n  After oversampling       : each class = 16.67% → fair learning\n  Minority classes (Sad, Fear, Surprise) now properly learned\n","output_type":"stream"}],"execution_count":90},{"id":"e6044aa0-905c-44f7-8325-5bf7fd4a0c1c","cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Insights visualization ─────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(13, 5))\n\n# Vectorizer comparison\ncolors_v = sns.color_palette('Set1', 3)\naxes[0].bar(vec_avg.index, vec_avg.values, color=colors_v, edgecolor='white', linewidth=1.5, width=0.55)\nfor i, (v, s) in enumerate(vec_avg.items()):\n    axes[0].text(i, s + 0.005, f'{s:.4f}', ha='center', fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\naxes[0].set_title('Average F1 Score by Vectorizer', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\naxes[0].set_ylabel('Average F1 Score'); axes[0].set_ylim(0, 1.1)\n\n# Model comparison\ncolors_m = sns.color_palette('Set2', 3)\naxes[1].bar(mod_avg.index, mod_avg.values, color=colors_m, edgecolor='white', linewidth=1.5, width=0.55)\nfor i, (m, s) in enumerate(mod_avg.items()):\n    axes[1].text(i, s + 0.005, f'{s:.4f}', ha='center', fontsize=10, fontweight='bold')\naxes[1].set_title('Average F1 Score by Model', fontsize=12, fontweight='bold')\naxes[1].set_ylabel('Average F1 Score'); axes[1].set_ylim(0, 1.1)\naxes[1].tick_params(axis='x', rotation=10)\n\nplt.suptitle('💡 Key Insights — Best Vectorizer & Best Model', fontsize=13, fontweight='bold')\nplt.tight_layout()\nplt.savefig('insights_chart.png', dpi=130, bbox_inches='tight')\nplt.show()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-28T09:46:35.523046Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-28T09:46:35.523254Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-28T09:46:35.971208Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-28T09:46:35.523234Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-28T09:46:35.969871Z"}},"outputs":[{"output_type":"display_data","data":{"text/plain":"<Figure size 1300x500 with 2 Axes>","image/png":"\n"},"metadata":{}}],"execution_count":91},{"id":"74d828c4-1ab4-4a72-9b13-c3f7880af94a","cell_type":"markdown","source":"### 📝 Final Insights Summary\n\n#### 🔤 Vectorization Analysis\n- **TF-IDF typically wins** because it assigns high weight to rare but emotion-specific words (e.g., *\"heartbroken\"* appears mostly in Sad tweets and gets high TF-IDF score).\n- **CountVectorizer** is similar to TF-IDF but treats all word occurrences equally — slightly weaker.\n- **Word2Vec** captures semantic meaning (e.g., *\"joyful\"* ≈ *\"happy\"*) but loses specificity through averaging.\n\n#### 🤖 Model Analysis\n- **Logistic Regression** excels on high-dimensional sparse text features — each word dimension gets a learned coefficient per emotion class.\n- **Linear SVC** creates optimal hyperplanes in feature space — extremely efficient for text with 5000+ features.\n- **Random Forest** works better with **dense Word2Vec** embeddings than sparse CountVec/TF-IDF because it makes binary splits that work poorly on mostly-zero sparse matrices.\n\n#### ⚖️ Imbalance Impact\n- Without oversampling: model would predict *Neutral* for ~90% of cases and still get 58% accuracy (misleading!).\n- With oversampling: model must learn all 6 emotions — F1 score is now a **honest** metric of performance.","metadata":{}},{"id":"94d44b6f-a77c-4884-a770-6c79c83a750b","cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n\n<div style=\"background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a2e, #16213e); padding: 30px; border-radius: 12px; text-align: center;\">\n  <h2 style=\"color: #64ffda; margin: 0;\">🎓 Assignment Complete!</h2>\n  <p style=\"color: #a8b2d8; margin-top: 12px;\">\n    Preprocessing ✅ | Balancing ✅ | Vectorization ✅ | Modeling ✅ | Evaluation ✅ | Gradio App ✅\n  </p>\n  <table style=\"margin: 16px auto; color: #ccd6f6; font-size: 0.9em;\">\n    <tr><td style=\"padding: 4px 16px;\">📊 Total Experiments</td><td><b style='color:#6